pattern_2.text: I think the experiment is trying to figure out whether our perception of size/huskiness which could be conflated with aggression and thus influence our fear of another person is effected by race. I'm guessing there was a bunch of pictures of different sized bodies generated with white skin and the same photos then duplicated for black skin. The hypothesis would be that people would subconsciously rate player's body with black skin as bigger/huskier and thus more threatening.
